33:
We are NOT! It's called observing!
That wicked witch is always up to
something, and it's our job to keep
an eye on her!
37:
I'm pretty sure you just described
stalking.
43:
No? Belsidia's more likely to hug
Stella to death than actually hurt
her.
47:
Even more reason to keep her under
surveillance then!
53:
Is it just me, or does he go kinda
nuts when it comes to that witch?
57:
Well, they did try to kill each other at
one point, so I can see where he's
coming from...
61: What is this suspicious looking place?
65:
If you wanna talk about sus, we're
the ones that stalked someone
here...
70: Alk is the sensible one, as ever.
74:
How far the champion must have
fallen if he's taken to peeping on
innocent maidens.
80:
Excuse me? That's your hobby, not
mine!
83:
Now answer me—what evil deed
have you brought Stella here for?!
116:
You've been so focused on your
heroic duties, you've lost touch with
the modern world... How sad.
121:
Sh-shush! I never had an interest in
these types of establishments in the
first place!
127:
As you can see, it's just a place to
take care of your skin so you can
look young and healthy.
130:
That's it? But why would the witch
need help with that?
136:
Oh? Is that a compliment I hear? I
didn't know you had it in you!
140:
We first met when I was 16, and she
hasn't aged a day since.
149:
There are also records of the Wicked
Witch of the Rift that can be traced
back to ancient times—
155: Okay, that's enough out of you.
158:
Stella, why don't we leave these two
to their stalking and get on with our
day?
160:
This place came highly
recommended by our resident
gunwielding beauty, so I'm sure the
service will be nothing to sneeze at.
169:
Since you're here anyway, why don't
you wait over there? You can judge
our makeovers once we're done.
174:
What exactly are we meant to do
while we wait though...
178:
Hey, Light, take a look at this. Says
they've got permanent hair removal
treatments.
203: My skin is as soft as pudding.
205: Even my cheeks are squishy. Look!
210:
I suppose it's no surprise that's the
part you care about.
214:
Are there other effects to the
treatment?
218:
None that you'll notice until you find
yourself standing in front of a mirror,
affectionately thinking of someone
else.
220:
...Maybe even of an impressive lady
who transcends the limits of mortals.
223:
But I think, my little caterpillar, a
metamorphosis is in order before
we can see that version of you.
228:
If change is what is needed, then I
believe I am qualified. I have been in
constant flux since I first left Starview.
231:
As for thinking affectionately of
someone else... Does thinking of you
not count?
235:
Oh, my! I didn't know you could be
so forward, darling!
238:
Oops, sorry! Don't want Alk getting
cross with me again.
243:
It is hard to breathe when you
squeeze so tightly...
248:
You've made a good point, though...
I suppose change requires more
than just love.
260:
Of course, honey. I can't wait to see
what you'll be like once you've finally
found the one!
265: I will try not to let you down.
270:
...Don't tell me those two completely
forgot about us.
